
[1]goldbeater

   GOLDBEATER, n. One whose occupation is to beat or foliate gold for
   gilding.

   Goldbeater's skin, the intestinum rectum of an ox, which goldbeaters
   lay between the leaves of the metal while they beat it, whereby the
   membrane is reduced very thin, and made fit to be applied to cuts and
   fresh wounds.
